top_comment.text:
Venho notando que vocês, Barbixas, decaíram no nível de humor de uma forma 
estrondosa, mas tenho que ser justo e dizer que este vídeo voltou a um 
certo nível de boa qualidade. Mantenha isso! Como fã de vocês, peço para 
que voltem as origens, pois o começo do improvável foi épico, até meados de 
2013 continuou top. Vocês tem talento de sobra, mas estão se acomodando com 
poder dizer qualquer coisa no palco, sem se importar com qualidade. Espero 
mais dessa temporada de vocês, como fã e espectador. Sei que assiste quem 
quer, já que eu mesmo disse, sou espectador, não sou obrigado, mas digo 
porque já me diverti demais com o trabalho de vocês, e quero mais disso, 
pois desejo muito que voltem a ser o #1 de humor do Brasil. Pra não acharem 
que sou apenas um fã atípico, assisti todos os vídeos, fora algumas 
apresentações. Abraço.﻿

captions.text:
"Soundtrack"!
Dani, Elidio and Allan!
Dani Tauszig is the boss of this game.

They will start the scene, and Tauszig
will start to play whenever he wants.

And the feeling, the timing,
the mood of the scene will change

according to Tauszig's keyboard.
Okay?

- Give me a place, please.
- Drugstore!

Drugstore, great.
'Drugstore' is the place, thank you.

It's "Soundtrack", the place is
a 'drugstore' and it starts now!
May I help?
Where do you keep the stuff for muscles?

- Do you want something for working out, or...
- No, a muscle relaxant.

- Muscle relaxant. Do you want
ointment or pills? - Pills.

Pills. Do you want
an ointment in pills?

Pills! The ones you put in the mouth,
swallow with a liquid and you get better.

I see. I only have the chewable
one, so you don't use a liquid...

Chewable is not the same thing.
It's like bubble gum.

- But I will get it for you!
- Please, hurry!

- It's on the fourth shelf, stay here!
- I won't move!
The head pharmacist saw me!
No sale without prescription!
Please, help me!
Oh, no!
We can't sell it without a prescription.

- But, I'm feeling bad, sir...
- Sorry, we're not authorized,

once a customer came
here with a headache,

we gave him a medicine for headache, then
his head exploded and we got the blame.

- So we don't sell without prescriptions anymore.
- Sorry, I was going to help you.

Can I have the ointment?
An ointment, for God's sake!

- Let him have the ointment, boss!
- Ointment!

- Let me go...
- He's in pain, boss, look!

- He's in pain...
- Damned prescriptions!

If I could have the prescription,
even on the internet,

you could send us, we would
print it and it would be fine.

It's a stiff neck,
a muscular contraction...

- Contra what?
- Muscular contraction!

Muscular contraction,
I've never heard of that!
Contraction, contraction...

- He's the head pharmacist?
- Yeah, he's the boss of the drugstore.
I see.

- We can sell this one without a
prescription, how about it? - I feel better!

- It's phytotherapy!
- It's much better!

- Alternative medicine is great!
- It's very good!

I'd like something else...
Do you have shampoo for hair loss?

Well, sou you're saying
your hair is falling?
I have a solution for you...
This one will get you up!
Soundtrack, ladies and gentlemen!

- Dani's got some moves, dude!
- You mean a lamppost's moves.

CIA. BARBIXAS DE HUMOR
presented
